<TEXT>
eds leads thruout to update with fridays meeting of shultz and 
deng no pickup 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
chinas senior leader deng xiaoping told visiting 
us secretary of state george shultz on friday that their two 
nations should lift relations to a higher plane in the interest 
of the whole world 
the 83yearold deng said at the opening of the talks with 
shultz that chineseamerican relations have improved steadily 
during the reagan presidency 
of course there are still some problems between us he 
said i think it is quite natural for two countries to have a 
divergent point of view or even have differences 
shultz held talks with chinese officials thursday on the 
cambodian conflict and chinese weapons sales to the middle east 
on friday however deng stressed common interests though 
china is one of the poorest countries in the world and the united 
states is one of the richest countries he said after all 
both of us are big countries 
we should bring our relationship to a higher plane in the 
interest of peace and the interest of the people of the world 
shultz said i have a very confident feeling that the 
relationship thats developed between the united states and china 
has broad bipartisan support and so we can expect real continuity 
in this relationship 
shultz arrived thursday for a twoday visit his fourth to china 
since he assumed his post in 1982 
the secretary also met friday with premier li peng before 
afternoon talks with communist party secretarygeneral zhao ziyang 
deng has retired from all his posts except chairmanship of the 
central military commission 
however he still wields considerable influence in the 
government and party he was apparently in good spirits friday 
smiling and going out of his way to shake hands with american 
security guards 
he told shultz who was on the sixth stop of a ninenation asian 
tour i think you are the busiest man on earth 
on thursday shultz met for more than three hours with foreign 
minister qian qichen for what the american side characterized as 
a very good exchange they discussed cambodia and the 
proliferation of weapons sales in developing countries 
qian emphasized that china does not support the return of the 
khmer rouge to a dominant role in cambodia following the withdrawal 
of vietnamese troops 
vietnam invaded cambodia in late 1978 to end a threeyear reign 
of terror by the khmer rouge it says it will pull out its 
estimated 120000 troops in the next few years the united states 
and southeast asian countries have expressed concern that the khmer 
rouge backed by chinese arms will step into the power vacuum 
however qian said thursday that some senior khmer rouge leaders 
may retire the remark suggested that pol pot and others associated 
with bloody policies of the mid70s will not play a role in any 
future cambodian government 
qian also said china foresees a potential role for an 
international peacekeeping force in cambodia both china and the 
united states have called for an immediate end to vietnams 
military occupation 
shultz in his talks with qian and at a later banquet speech 
spoke in general terms of the dangers of introducing sophisticated 
weapons into the middle east and other unstable regions 
but us sources speaking on condition of anonymity said he 
did not specifically criticize china for selling intermediaterange 
ballistic missiles to mideast countries while moscow and washington 
are eliminating such weapons from their arsenals shultz had made 
such criticism earlier on his tour 
shultz said in his banquet speech it is ironic that just as 
the major powers are making progress in getting their arms 
competition under some control the developing world is 
increasingly burdened by this flow of advanced weaponry 
the united states is concerned that china a major arms supplier 
to iran iraq and other middle east nations has sold the css2 
missile to saudi arabia and is developing and already marketing the 
m9 missile in the region 
according to us figures china sold about 2 billion worth of 
arms last year 
qian was quoted as telling shultz that china sells only 
defensive weapons that contribute to peace and regional stability 
shultz also applauded recent south korean moves to ease tensions 
on the korean peninsula and called on north korea to respond and 
help ensure a safe and successful olympic games in seoul the 
souths capital this fall china is a close ally of communist 
north korea 
shultz was scheduled to leave saturday morning for seoul his 
tour was also to take him to japan and the marshall islands 
</TEXT>
