welfare of a child in the plea agreement was given probation 
wednesday because it was his first offense said bergen county 
superior court judge james madden he could have received a 
fiveyear prison term 
i am not condoning what this young man did madden said 
however there are mitigating circumstances extreme 
mitigating circumstances 
waltman 24 of alloway township was arrested outside giants 
stadium in east rutherford in march 1987 when he attempted to sell 
daughter rachel now 6 years old to her uncle gary stern police 
tipped off by stern were waiting for waltman in the new york city 
suburb 
waltmans attorney james patuto said his client was a victim 
of pressures brought on him in a battle over rachels custody with 
other family members 
