evidence introduced today 
chief judge heiner mueckenberger read a document from 
authorities in lebanon that said an arrest warrant was issued for 
the defendant in 1983 on charges of murder and unlawful use of 
weapons 
the document did not contain details of the alleged crimes and 
hamadi said i dont know anything about it 
the twa jetliner on an athenstorome flight was hijacked in 
june 1985 us navy diver robert stethem of waldorf md was 
killed after the hijackers forced the plane to land in beirut 
thirtynine americans were held hostage during the 17day ordeal 
hamadi who came to west germany in 1982 also testified today 
that he worked at a cemetery in saarlouis in 1983 while his 
application for political asylum was pending 
he said he tried to commit suicide once by swallowing pills in 
1983 and once before by slashing his wrists because he was 
depressed about his life in west germany and because of 
developments in lebanon 
hamadi has said he returned to lebanon in 1984 in part because 
his application for political asylum was not approved 
a shiite moslem hamadi testified wednesday that he belonged to 
the shiite amal militia between 1980 and 1982 in beirut and was 
involved in battles there 
but he denied involvement with hezbollah or party of god a 
radical proiranian shiite moslem group believed to be the umbrella 
organization for gunmen holding foreign hostages in lebanon 
one of hamadis brothers abdulhadi hamadi is chief of 
security for hezbollah in beirut another abbas ali hamadi was 
convicted in april of kidnapping two west germans in lebanon in an 
attempt to win mohammeds freedom he was sentenced to 13 years in 
prison by a duesseldort court 
speaking in arabic hamadi told the court today that while 
living in beirut he had been trained to fight as an amal member 
i was forced by circumstances to carry weapons i wanted to 
fight against israel hamadi said making his first statements to 
the frankfurt court since his trial began last week 
there is a saying in our country in lebanon you are born 
with a weapon in your hand he said 
hamadi said he was trained by amal to use a rocketpropelled 
grenade launcher and other weapons 
asked whether he had owned hand grenades hamadi answered 
everyone had these at home you could buy them like you buy 
eggs 
he told the court he had smuggled liquid explosives into west 
germany twice contradicting a statement he made to police after 
his january 1987 arrest at the time hamadi told police he thought 
the bottles were filled with alcohol and denied knowing that they 
contained high explosives 
a certain person asked me to smuggle them in and hide them 
hamadi said i did it twice the second time i was arrested 
i dont know the reason why the explosives were brought in i was 
not told 
hamadi was accused of involvement in the hijacking based on 
evidence that includes fingerprints west germany last year 
rejected a us request for his extradition 
hamadi is being tried under heavy security in a specially 
constructed prison courtroom 
