chairman markey conceded the measure may not have a chance until 
next year 
rohatyn an advisor to the prospective democratic presidential 
candidate massachusetts gov michael dukakis went beyond voicing 
support for markeys bill which would empower the securities and 
exchange commission to regulate index futures now overseen by the 
commodity fsutures trading commission 
rohatyn suggested a series of taxes and other measures that he 
said would dampen speculation by large institutional investors 
controlling billions of dollars including pension funds insurance 
companies banks and other governmentbacked entities 
the fundamental weakness in the securities markets 
worldwide is the result of excessive speculation excessive use 
of credit and inadequate regulation rohatyn said 
rohatyn a partner at lazard freres amp co in new york said that 
market speculation is driven by large institutions which he said 
are risking the assets of retirees depositors and policy 
holders and also putting the taxpayers at risk 
rohatyn proposed 50 percent taxes on the profits from the sales 
of securities held less than one year reducing capital gains taxes 
on securities held more than five years limiting the types of 
investments governmentinsured institutions could make and other 
changes 
i am aware of the political difficulties of such a program 
he said i am resigned to the reality that it will not happen 
until the next market crisis 
