south african and cuban 
officials said thursday that major issues remain unresolved 
following a milestone agreement aimed at easing conflict in angola 
and southwest africa 
south africas foreign minister roelof f botha said president 
pw botha who are not related will preside over a government 
meeting next week to decide whether to accept the principles agreed 
upon by delegates after three days of talks in new york 
a cuban official in new york said a us mediators assertion 
that agreement in principle had been reached on a cuban withdrawal 
from angola was inexact this issue remained under discussion 
the cuban said 
state department and south african officials at the united 
nations in new york however on thursday called it merely a matter 
of semantics they said cuba did agree to bring its troops home 
but expressed that in a statement of principles not in what 
diplomats would call an agreement 
the officials spoke on condition of anonymity 
on wednesday us assistant secretary of state chester crocker 
said angolan cuban and south african negotiators agreed on a set 
of principles aimed at removing cuban troops from angola and ending 
south africas 73year rule over southwest africa also known as 
namibia 
the agreement will be referred back to the three governments if 
they approve another round of negotiations probably would be held 
next month 
the negotiators did not resolve the most contentious issue a 
timetable for the cuban withdrawal and implementation of un 
resolution 435 which outlines a procedure for granting 
independence to namibia 
on thursday a cuban delegate differed with crockers account of 
the talks 
it is not precise to say that an agreement has been reached on 
the withdrawal of cuban troops said alcibiades hidalgo a member 
of the central committee of cubas communist party 
this issue is part of all the discussions is part of a 
process that is continuing he said it is our opinion that we 
made substantial progress 
the agreement linking the withdrawal of cuban forces from 
angola to south african withdrawal from namibia received lowkey 
treatment in south africa 
the road is still far that we have to travel but as of now 
the momentum and confidence have been established to enable us to 
continue neil van heerden directorgeneral of foreign affairs 
and head of the south african delegation was quoted as saying 
crocker said the negotiators in new york decided it was not yet 
time to address the timing of the cuban withdrawal 
south africa and the united states would like to see the 
estimated 50000 cubans leave angola within a year the same 
timetable the united nations has suggested for south african 
withdrawal from namibia 
the cubans and angolans have said in the past it would take four 
years and that south african and american military support for the 
unita guerrillas must end first unita stands for the national 
union for the total independence of angola 
one of the first steps would be withdrawal of south african 
troops from angola south africa has said it has a maximum of about 
3000 troops in angola while its foes claimed 9000 south africans 
were there last year fighting alongside unita 
more than 45 white south african soldiers have died in angola in 
the past year and each death brings more domestic pressure on the 
government to justify its military policy 
crocker said the south african administration in namibia would 
be replaced by un civil and military administrators to comply 
with un resolution 435 south africa has said it would accept the 
resolution only after the cubans leave angola 
in washington un ambassador vernon walters told cbs this 
morning that many obstacles remain 
this war has been going on for 15 years theres a whole lot 
of hostility built up he said 
the united states was a party to the talks because it has been 
supporting unita with funds and weapons since 1985 
asked if the united states would continue backing the rebels 
walters said thats a decision taken in the light of 
circumstances 
the 13yearold civil war in angola despite the presence of 
cuban and south african troops is chiefly between the marxist 
government forces and unita 
in namibia the southwest african peoples organization has been 
fighting a guerrilla war for 22 years to end south african 
occupation and gain control of an independent government 
