<TEXT>
this is one of a series of periodic reports by 
associated press correspondents on people places and things in 
other countries 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the veiled arab woman checked in at the 
desk reeboks peeping from under her abaya the black shroudlike 
robe moslem women wear 
in the locker room she shed the robe to reveal the latest in 
latex exercise gear within minutes she was gyrating to the 
pounding beat of the aerobics class music 
physical fitness is a sensitive subject in the arab world where 
religion and custom decree that womens bodies and sometimes their 
faces be covered 
even in the relatively westernized arab states on the persian 
gulf many women young and old adhere to tradition walking the 
streets in their abayas 
but the female fitness craze has arrived and among gulf women 
it is just beginning to hit its stride 
in another manama gym a young girl in red stretch jogging pants 
and a tshirt reading bye bye worry is one of 33 arab women 
all physical fitness instructors taking a training seminar 
the women 19 to 34 years old have been training for two years 
and now teach their own community courses currently drawing about 
1300 women 
kathy james an american sports specialist and guest instructor 
for the seminar sponsored by the us information service and the 
bahrain sports institute says she was surprised to find such an 
active group in the arab world 
i think theyre becoming more aware of how important it is to 
keep your body physically fit she said 
medical experts say oil wealth and other factors beginning in 
the 1970s have helped bring about changes in eating habits 
saturated fats refined sugars and processed foods have become part 
of the diet and people are adopting a luxuryloving more sedentary 
lifestyle 
its overindulgence said dr essa amin chief of the 
medical staff at bahrains defense force hospital 
theres definitely a link between the diet habit the lack of 
exercise and higher incidence of diabetes cardiac and 
cardiocirculatory problems 
interest in fitness has been encouraged by european and other 
expatriate women who bring a more active sportsoriented lifestyle 
to the region 
apart from those operated at major hotels bahrain now has about 
15 womens fitness centers in schools gymnasiums and private 
health clubs and health studios also operate in nearby dubai and 
abu dhabi 
in cairo egypt aerobics instructor samia allouba has kept her 
popular television show going despite islamic fundamentalist 
opposition that she says has included telephone threats and 
street taunts from both men and women 
she compromises by wearing discreet highcollared tops with 
long sleeves during her tv presentations 
but having crusaded for female fitness for eight years she now 
thinks shes winning egyptian as well as foreign women fill her 
suburban cairo studio from morning to night 
in the last two years ive noticed a definite change in the 
attitudes of women she said in a telephone interview theyve 
become more interested in becoming healthy 
odette alagasi aerobics instructor at bahrains gulf hotel 
said that when she arrived from the philippines more than a year 
ago virtually all her students were foreign women now at least 
onefourth are local 
alagasi 24 said most of her students enroll to lose weight and 
arent aware of such things as the cardiovascular benefits of 
exercise 
mona alansari 29 who has trained the 33 aerobics and fitness 
instructors for the bahrain governments council for youth and 
sports says arab women naturally shy are more at ease in being 
taught by another arab 
we understand their special needs they trust us to do 
their classes for them she said before they didnt have the 
chance to do anything like this for themselves now the opportunity 
is there 
wives mothers and girls women from 12 to 60 years old are 
coming to classes and i like to encourage the women to do sports 
to be on a level with the men 
the advocates of exercise say they see is no conflict with the 
teachings of islam 
instructor alansari quotes the prophet mohammed as saying 
the strong moslem is better than the weak moslem 
</TEXT>
