<DOCNO> AP880714-0228 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
rein and sirje ruutsoo are estonias 
version of the children of the 1960s they wanted to take on the 
establishment but this was the soviet union 
they had hopes for a revival of estonian culture and political 
power during the liberalization drive of nikita s khrushchev after 
years of stalinism but khrushchev was ousted in 1964 and leonid i 
brezhnev rose to kremlin leadership and any hopes the ruutsoos had 
were quickly dashed 
now with mikhail s gorbachev leading the nation and opening up 
a closed society the ruutsoos are speaking their minds 
so are many of their fellow estonians and people living in the 
two neighboring soviet republics on the baltic sea latvia and 
lithuania 
they want officials in moscow to keep their hands off the 
culture language and economy of the baltic states home for 77 
million people 
by allowing the soviet unions many nationalities to vent long 
pentup demands gorbachev may gain popular support in estonia and 
other independentminded republics 
estonia with a 15 million population is already among the 
most westernized of the 15 soviet republics 
along with latvia and lithuania estonia had a brief taste of 
independence 22 years between the two world wars and still 
feels some kinship with the finns who live just 50 miles across the 
gulf of finland and whose language is akin to estonian 
but estonians lithuanians and latvians have lived under the 
influence or domination of others since the 13th century starting 
with the german teutonic order then came the swedes followed by 
the czarists russians in the early 18th century with the collapse 
of the russian monarchy and the defeat of germany in world war i 
the baltic states proclaimed independence in 1918 but under a 
secret agreement with nazi germany josef stalins soviet union 
annexed the baltic states in 1940 
today switzerlandsized estonia is on the front line of 
gorbachevs battle to build citizens economic and political 
initiative 
signs that estonians are taking up his battle cry of 
perestroika gorbachevs policy of restructuring of society 
are all about tallinn the picturesque ancient seaside capital 
shops display colorful westernstyle fashions unseen in other 
soviet stores 
estonians march with their previously banned black blue and 
white national flag 
a nationalist emblem carved in stone on a city building but 
covered up for as long as anyone can remember has suddenly 
reappeared 
the greens environmental group branching out from west 
germany has painted slogans with ecological demands on a barricade 
wall at a construction site 
longbanned plays with nationalist themes are allowed and 
interest in folk choirs has been renewed a cultural 
renaissance is taking place says a musician 
and the ruutsoos after years of underground activism that began 
at tartu university estonias spawning ground for many cultural 
figures they now are central figures in a group called the 
peoples front for perestroika 
all the peoples front leaders are idealists of the 1960s 
explained rein ruutsoo a 41yearold philosopher and communist 
party member the 60s generation hoped to take over the communist 
party we had some illusions now its our second chance 
ruutsoo who refuses to speak russian to protest encroachment of 
the soviet unions largest and most influential republic on 
estonian life explained in english that he was among 40 estonian 
intellectuals who signed a letter in 1980 protesting what they saw 
as the russification of their culture 
the kgb secret police accused his 39yearold wife sirje of 
being a us central intelligence agent for collecting half the 
signatures on the letter two years later she was expelled from 
the communist party for writing a poem in which the first letters 
of each line spelled the colors of the estonian flag 
in those days estonian television announcers were not permitted 
to refer to the region as estonia in weather reports the ruutsoos 
recalled between sips of tea grown in the garden of their home 
they called it just the republic or the baltic area 
throughout the ruutsoos house which has been in reins family 
for four generations is evidence that times have changed 
an estonian flag sits atop the television set and they showed a 
reporter a tshirt imprinted with a map of estonia and the words in 
english go home strangers meaning the russians 
gorbachev has said the kremlin was mistaken in the past to 
suppress national cultures and languages like estonias 
he has promised to be more sensitive to the soviet unions more 
than 100 ethnic groups some of which are now among the most ardent 
practitioners of his glasnost openness epolicy using it to 
express their longrepressed national or ethnic identities 
the peoples front for perestroika is one outgrowth of the new 
tolerance it sprang up in april when the estonian philosopher 
edgar savisaar proposed on television creating a democratic 
movement to support perestroika the group now has 900 affiliates 
with 50000 members in estonia ruutsoo said and sister 
organizations have been formed in latvia and lithuania 
while generally supporting communist party policies the 
peoples front demands political and economic sovereignty of 
union republics and cultural autonomy for all nationalities 
it calls for direct estonian trade ties outside of moscows 
control with foreign companies and says it intends to propose 
legislation and up candidates for government posts the only 
condition for membership is active and businesslike support of 
the course of perestroika 
at first the established leadership in estonia apparently 
fearing a challenge to its authority denied the new group access 
to the republiccontrolled press 
but on june 16 the republics party chief karl vaino a 
holdover from the brezhnev years was replaced by vajno vyalyas a 
gorbachev protege and former soviet ambassador to nicaragua who 
already had respect among estonian intellectuals 
the next day 150000 people gathered in a meadow outside 
tallinn to show their support for the peoples front and to ask 
estonias delegates to the nationa communist party conference in 
moscow to press the groups demands 
the delegation led by vyalyas endorsed the fronts demands for 
local control over the republics finances environmental policy 
culture and education and pleaded their case before the 5000 
communists who assembled in the kremlin june 28july 1 to set party 
policy 
the delegations platform also calls for limiting migration to 
estonia where ethnic estonians now make up just 60 percent of the 
population the republic was 90percent estonian in 1940 
the estonian delegates to the party conference in moscow appear 
to have won much of what they sought at least in principle the 
conference adopted a resolution saying republics were entitled to 
greater independence in economic social cultural and ecological 
spheres 
the peoples front stops short however of calling for 
secession from the soviet union but ruutsoo says its generally 
assumed the goal is a revival of an independent estonia 
sirje ruutsoo doesnt conceal her own thoughts 
its a revolution she said the only thing is tanks are 
on the other side thats the only reason we dont have a new 
republic already 
</TEXT>
