<TEXT>
crude oil prices have slumped to a 21month low 
amid growing pessimism about overproduction by opec members 
on the new york mercantile exchange the augustdelivery price 
of west texas intermediate crude which fell 6 cents on tuesday 
fell another 28 cents wednesday to close at 1444 per barrel 
the last time prices for the near month wti contract were lower 
was oct 29 1986 when they closed at 1373 a barrel 
fears of continued overproduction by the organization of 
petroleum exporting countries sent prices lower said andrew lebow 
senior broker and analyst at edampf man international futures inc 
its the same type of scenario thats burdened the market for 
the last couple of weeks he said 
among refined products traded on the exchange the august 
contract for wholesale unleaded tumbled 3 cents to close at 5048 
cents a gallon 
gasoline futures had fared better than oil in recent weeks 
because of increased demand during the summer driving season but 
profittaking and rumors that importers were buying foreign 
gasoline to ease tight supplies took their toll on gas prices 
wednesday lebow said 
