the bull market is being driven by tight supplies worldwide and 
fears of drought damage to the us sugar beet crop 
the markets gone berserk said erik dunlaevy a trader for 
balfour maclaine corp in new york 
sugar for october delivery settled 71 cent higher at 1527 
cents a pound 
