general motors corp announced thursday it is 
recalling about 155000 model 198688 cars to correct a variety of 
problems including brake wiring and fuel filler neck difficulties 
the automaker said it is not aware of any accidents or injuries 
attributed to the problems owners will be notified to take their 
cars to dealers who will make the necessary repairs at no charge 
gm said 
dealers will inspect about 73000 model 1988 pontiac lemans for 
defects in fuel filler neck construction the condition could cause 
fuel to leak from the filler neck mechanism in excess of federal 
safety standards gm said 
on 65000 model 1986 and 1987 buick rivieras and oldsmobile 
toronados a problem with the power steering pump hose could cause 
a fluid leak gm said dealers will replace the hose with another 
pump mechanism 
about 15000 model 1988 chevrolet cavalier and pontiac sunbird 
coupes and convertibles may have faulty rear lamp wiring that could 
cause backup lamps to flash or render them inoperative gm said 
dealers will make the necessary wiring changes 
about 1900 model 1987 and 1988 buick lesabres with antilock 
brake systems could lose brake functions over time gm said 
dealers will tighten hydraulic unit mounting bolts to correct the 
problem the automaker said 
about 430 model 1988 oldsmobile 98 touring sedans have a problem 
that could prevent the driver from seeing the shift indicator in 
the dark or bump it into another gear dealers will replace a clip 
to assure the indicator is properly positioned gm said 
